[docs]def product_sij_sji(sij,sji):
    J2=np.zeros((sij.shape[0]))
    for k in range(sij.shape[0]):
        sum=0.
        for i in range(3):
            for j in range(3):
                sum+=sij[k,i,j]*sji[k,i,j]
        J2[k]=sum
    return J2

    

[docs]def calculate_J2(sigma11,sigma22,sigma33,sigma23,sigma13,sigma12):
    p_tot=(sigma11+sigma22+sigma33)/3.
    s11=sigma11-p_tot
    s22=sigma22-p_tot
    s33=sigma33-p_tot
    s23=sigma23
    s13=sigma13
    s12=sigma12
        
    sij=np.array(np.zeros((s11.shape[0],3,3)))
    sij[:,0,0]=s11
    sij[:,0,1]=s12
    sij[:,1,0]=-s12

    sij[:,1,1]=s22
    sij[:,0,2]=s13
    sij[:,2,0]=-s13

    sij[:,2,2]=s33
    sij[:,1,2]=s23
    sij[:,2,1]=-s23
    
    sji=np.array(np.zeros(sij.shape))
    sji[:]=np.transpose(sij,axes=(0,2,1))
    
    J2=np.sqrt(1./2.*product_sij_sji(sij,sji))
    return J2



[docs]def calculate_dissipation(sigma11,sigma22,sigma33,sigma23,sigma31,sigma12,epsilon11,epsilon22,epsilon33,gamma32,gamma31,gamma12):
    epsilon12=gamma12/2.
    epsilon31=gamma31/2.
    epsilon32=gamma32/2.

    epsilon21=gamma12/2.
    epsilon13=gamma31/2.
    epsilon23=gamma32/2.

    
    W11=sigma11*epsilon11
    W22=sigma22*epsilon22
    W33=sigma33*epsilon33

    W12=sigma12*epsilon12+sigma12*epsilon21
    W13=sigma31*epsilon31+sigma31*epsilon13
    W23=sigma23*epsilon23+sigma23*epsilon32
    
    dissipation= W11+W22+W33+W12+W13+W23
    return dissipation

[docs]    def test_generalized_force_displacement_values(self):
        '''
        Tests calculated nodal forces and displacements to values in ./reference_data/Cauchy3D_THM_Hydroplasticity.out
        '''
        self.my_FEproblem1.extract_generalized_force_disp()
        values_time1 = self.my_FEproblem1.array_time
        values_gen_force1 = self.my_FEproblem1.array_gen_force
        values_gen_disp1 = self.my_FEproblem1.array_gen_disp
        
        sigma11= np.sum(values_gen_force1[:,0:4].copy(),axis=1)
        sigma22= np.sum(values_gen_force1[:,4:8].copy(),axis=1)
        sigma33= np.sum(values_gen_force1[:,8:12].copy(),axis=1)
        sigma23= np.sum(values_gen_force1[:,12:16].copy(),axis=1)
        sigma13= np.sum(values_gen_force1[:,16:20].copy(),axis=1)
        sigma12= np.sum(values_gen_force1[:,20:24].copy(),axis=1)
        
        J2_1=calculate_J2(sigma11,sigma22,sigma33,sigma23,sigma13,sigma12)
        
        self.my_FEproblem2.extract_generalized_force_disp()
        values_time2      = self.my_FEproblem2.array_time
        values_gen_force2 = self.my_FEproblem2.array_gen_force
        values_gen_disp2  = self.my_FEproblem2.array_gen_disp
        
        sigma11= np.sum(values_gen_force2[:,0:4].copy(),axis=1)
        sigma22= np.sum(values_gen_force2[:,4:8].copy(),axis=1)
        sigma33= np.sum(values_gen_force2[:,8:12].copy(),axis=1)
        sigma23= np.sum(values_gen_force2[:,12:16].copy(),axis=1)
        sigma13= np.sum(values_gen_force2[:,16:20].copy(),axis=1)
        sigma12= np.sum(values_gen_force2[:,20:24].copy(),axis=1)
        
        J2_2=calculate_J2(sigma11,sigma22,sigma33,sigma23,sigma13,sigma12)
        
        values1=np.concatenate((values_time1, values_gen_disp1, values_gen_force1), axis=1)
    
        # with open(reference_data_path+"Cauchy3D_THM_Hydroplasticity.out", "wb") as fp:   #Pickling
        #     pickle.dump(values1,fp)        
    
        with open(reference_data_path+"Cauchy3D_THM_Hydroplasticity.out", "rb") as fp:   #Pickling
            values_ref=pickle.load(fp)        
        values_diff=values_ref-values1
    
        equal=abs(np.linalg.norm(values_diff))<=1.e-13
        self.assertTrue(equal, "Not identical time, displacements, forces: "+str(abs(np.linalg.norm(values_diff))))
        #asserts that data are correct
        #if data are correct then plot diagram
        if equal and activate_plots:
            x1=list(values_time1[:].copy())
            y1=J2_1.tolist()
            x1.insert(0,0)
            y1.insert(0,0)
    
            fig, ax1, color1 = plotting_params.object_plot_axes('$t$ [s]', y1_txt='$\sqrt{J_2}$ [MPa]',color1='',y2_txt='',color2='', title='',mode='1')
    
            plotting_params.object_plot(x1, y1, "y1", ax1, 'ax2', mode='1',color1=color1,color2='color2',label_string='')
            plotting_params.show_plot()           
            plotting_params.plot_legends(ngeo_parameters.reference_data_path, fig, filename='Cauchy_3D_Hydroplasticity_0_P',mode='1')
    
    
            x1=list(values_time1[:].copy())
            y1=list(values_gen_disp1[:,3].copy()+values_gen_disp1[:,7].copy()+values_gen_disp1[:,11].copy())
            x1.insert(0,0)
            y1.insert(0,0)
    
            fig, ax1, color1 = plotting_params.object_plot_axes('$t$ [s]', y1_txt='$\\varepsilon_{v}$',color1='',y2_txt='',color2='', title='',mode='1')
            plotting_params.object_plot(x1, y1, "y1", ax1, 'ax2', mode='1',color1=color1,color2='color2',label_string='')
            plotting_params.show_plot()           
            plotting_params.plot_legends(ngeo_parameters.reference_data_path, fig, filename='Cauchy_3D_Hydroplasticity_0_evol',mode='1')
    
            x1=list(values_time1[:].copy())
            y1=J2_1.tolist()
            x1.insert(0,0)
            y1.insert(0,0)
    
            x2=list(values_time1[:].copy())
            y2=J2_2.tolist()
            x2.insert(0,0)
            y2.insert(0,0)
    
            x3=list(values_time1[:].copy())
            y3=J2_2.tolist()
            x3.insert(0,0)

            plotting_params.object_plot(x2, y2, y1, ax1, 'ax2',x1, mode='3',color1=color1,color2='',label_string='')

[docs]    def check_yielding_criterion(self):
        self.my_FEproblem1.extract_generalized_force_disp()

        values_gen_force1 = self.my_FEproblem1.array_gen_force
        
        sigma11= np.sum(values_gen_force1[:,0:4].copy(),axis=1)
        sigma22= np.sum(values_gen_force1[:,4:8].copy(),axis=1)
        sigma33= np.sum(values_gen_force1[:,8:12].copy(),axis=1)
        sigma23= np.sum(values_gen_force1[:,12:16].copy(),axis=1)
        sigma13= np.sum(values_gen_force1[:,16:20].copy(),axis=1)
        sigma12= np.sum(values_gen_force1[:,20:24].copy(),axis=1)
        
        J2_1=calculate_J2(sigma11,sigma22,sigma33,sigma23,sigma13,sigma12)
        
        p_tot=(sigma11+sigma22+sigma33)/3.
        
        tanfi=self.my_FEproblem1.mats[0].props[10]
        F=J2_1-tanfi*p_tot
        equal=abs(np.linalg.norm(F))<=1.e-13
        self.assertTrue(equal, "Not identical time, displacements, forces: "+str(abs(np.linalg.norm(F))))

        

if __name__ == '__main__':
    unittest.main()
